Compilation Instructions for Syft using CMake

==== Install CUDD ====

0.1 Make sure CUDD is installed. CUDD can be found by:
    wget ftp://vlsi.colorado.edu/pub/cudd-3.0.0.tar.gz
    tar -xf cudd-3.0.0.tar.gz
    cd cudd-3.0.0

0.2 Install CUDD:
    ./configure --enable-slient-rules -enable-obj --enable-dddmp
    sudo make install

==== Install FLEX, BISON ====

0.3 Install flex and bison:
    sudo apt-get install flex bison

==== Install Syft ====

1. Make build folder so your directory is not flooded with build files:

   mkdir build && cd build

2. Run CMake to generate the makefile:

   cmake ..

3. Compile using the generated makefile:

   make
